    <div class="terms-content">
        <section class="mb-4">
            <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
            <p>
                Welcome to Streamtunes ("we," "our," or "us"). We are committed to protecting your privacy and personal 
                information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information 
                when you visit our website at <a href="https://streamtunes.net" target="_blank">https://streamtunes.net</a> 
                (the "Service") and use our music streaming and sales platform.
            </p>
            <p>
                Streamtunes is operated as a business registered in the State of Nevada, United States. By using the 
                Service, you consent to the data practices described in this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with 
                the practices described in this Privacy Policy, please do not use the Service.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-4">
            <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
            
            <h3>2.1 Information You Provide Directly</h3>
            <p>When you create an account or use our Service, we may collect the following information:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>Email Address:</strong> Required for account registration, login, communication, and 
                    email verification. Your email serves as your primary account identifier.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Password:</strong> Required for account security. Passwords are securely hashed using 
                    industry-standard cryptographic algorithms and are never stored in plain text.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Passkey Credentials:</strong> If you choose to use passkey authentication (WebAuthn/FIDO2), 
                    we store your public key credentials, attestation data, and related metadata necessary for secure 
                    passwordless authentication. Private keys never leave your device.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Theme Preferences:</strong> Your selected display theme preference (Light or Dark mode).
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h3>2.2 Information Collected Automatically</h3>
            <p>When you access the Service, we may automatically collect certain information:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>Usage Data:</strong> Information about how you interact with the Service, including songs 
                    you preview, listen to, like, dislike, add to playlists, or purchase.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Technical Data:</strong> Device information, browser type, operating system, and IP address 
                    collected through standard web server logs and analytics.
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h3>2.3 Information We Do NOT Collect</h3>
            <p>We want to be clear about the information we do NOT collect:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>We do NOT collect your name, physical address, phone number, or date of birth.</li>
                <li>We do NOT collect or store your complete payment card details (these are handled exclusively by PayPal).</li>
                <li>We do NOT collect location data beyond what may be inferred from IP addresses.</li>
                <li>We do NOT use cookies for third-party advertising or tracking across other websites.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-4">
            <h2>3. Payment Processing and PayPal Integration</h2>
            <p>
                All payment transactions on Streamtunes are processed through PayPal, a third-party payment processor. 
                When you make a purchase or subscribe to our service:
            </p>
            
            <h3>3.1 Information Shared with PayPal</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Order Details:</strong> The purchase amount and order reference ID</li>
                <li><strong>Currency:</strong> Transactions are processed in U.S. Dollars (USD)</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>3.2 Information We Receive from PayPal</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Order ID:</strong> A unique identifier for each transaction</li>
                <li><strong>Transaction Status:</strong> Whether the payment was completed, cancelled, or failed</li>
                <li><strong>Subscription ID:</strong> For monthly subscriptions, PayPal provides a subscription identifier</li>
                <li><strong>Payment Timestamps:</strong> When payments were made and next billing dates</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>3.3 What We Store</h3>
            <p>We store the following payment-related information in our database:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>PayPal order IDs and subscription IDs (not your PayPal account details)</li>
                <li>Transaction amounts and status</li>
                <li>Purchase history (which songs/albums you own)</li>
                <li>Subscription status and billing dates</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>3.4 PayPal's Privacy Practices</h3>
            <p>
                PayPal collects and processes payment information according to their own privacy policy. We encourage 
                you to review <a href="https://www.paypal.com/us/legalhub/privacy-full" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">PayPal's Privacy Policy</a> 
                to understand how they handle your financial information. We do not have access to your PayPal account 
                credentials, bank account numbers, or complete credit card details.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-4">
            <h2>4. How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p>We use the information we collect for the following purposes:</p>
            
            <h3>4.1 Account Management</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Creating and maintaining your user account</li>
                <li>Authenticating your identity when you log in</li>
                <li>Sending email verification and password reset messages</li>
                <li>Processing account changes and deletions</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>4.2 Service Provision</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Providing access to music streaming and purchases</li>
                <li>Managing your playlists and preferences</li>
                <li>Processing purchases and subscriptions</li>
                <li>Displaying your purchase history and owned content</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>4.3 Service Improvement</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Understanding how users interact with our Service</li>
                <li>Improving the functionality and user experience</li>
                <li>Developing new features and services</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>4.4 Communication</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Sending transactional emails (verification, purchase confirmations, subscription updates)</li>
                <li>Responding to your inquiries and support requests</li>
                <li>Notifying you of important changes to our Service or policies</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>4.5 Security and Legal Compliance</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Protecting against fraudulent, unauthorized, or illegal activity</li>
                <li>Enforcing our Terms of Use</li>
                <li>Complying with legal obligations</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-4">
            <h2>5. Information Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
            <p>We take your privacy seriously and limit how we share your information:</p>
            
            <h3>5.1 We Do NOT Sell Your Personal Information</h3>
            <p>
