            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-4">
            <h2>6. Data Security</h2>
            <p>
                We implement appropriate technical and organizational security measures to protect your personal 
                information against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>Password Security:</strong> Passwords are hashed using industry-standard cryptographic 
                    algorithms (ASP.NET Core Identity's default password hasher). We never store passwords in plain text.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Passkey Security:</strong> Passkey authentication uses public key cryptography. Your 
                    private keys never leave your device, and we only store the public key portion.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Encryption:</strong> Data transmitted between your browser and our servers is encrypted 
                    using HTTPS/TLS.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Access Controls:</strong> Access to personal information is restricted to authorized 
                    personnel who need it to operate, develop, or improve our Service.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Secure Infrastructure:</strong> Our Service is hosted on secure cloud infrastructure 
                    with appropriate security certifications and compliance measures.
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                While we strive to protect your information, no method of transmission over the Internet or 
                electronic storage is 100% secure. We cannot guarantee absolute security.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-4">
            <h2>7. Data Retention</h2>
            <p>We retain your information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>Active Accounts:</strong> Your account information is retained as long as your account 
                    remains active.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Purchase Records:</strong> Transaction history is retained to maintain your access to 
                    purchased content and for legal/accounting purposes.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Account Deletion:</strong> When you delete your account, we delete your personal 
                    information, including your email, password hash, passkey credentials, purchase history, 
                    playlists, and preferences. Some information may be retained in backups for a limited period 
                    or as required by law.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-4">
            <h2>8. Your Rights and Choices</h2>
            <p>You have certain rights regarding your personal information:</p>
            
            <h3>8.1 Access Your Information</h3>
            <p>
                You can access and review the personal information we hold about you through your account 
                management page.
            </p>

            <h3>8.2 Update Your Information</h3>
            <p>
                You can update your email address, password, and preferences through your account settings.
            </p>

            <h3>8.3 Delete Your Account</h3>
            <p>
                You have the right to delete your account at any time through your account management page. 
                Please note that account deletion is permanent and will result in the loss of all your 
                purchased content and playlists.
            </p>

            <h3>8.4 Passkey Management</h3>
            <p>
                You can add, remove, or rename passkeys associated with your account at any time through 
                your account management page.
            </p>

            <h3>8.5 Subscription Cancellation</h3>
            <p>
                You can cancel your subscription at any time through your account management page. After 
                cancellation, you will retain access until the end of your current billing period.
            </p>

            <h3>8.6 Communication Preferences</h3>
            <p>
                You will receive essential transactional emails (verification, purchase confirmations, 
                important account notices) as necessary for the operation of the Service. You cannot opt 
                out of these essential communications while maintaining an account.
            </p>
        </section>

